yes Jim, it is deplorable how little initiative is demonstrated here. I find it nearly impossible to understand how people can run a search for FSX software then only populate the results found on the first page - it is almost staggering. Whittman Tailwind, Hughes Racer and Junkers W-33 are three titles I can think of off the top of my head that have disappeared from TPB.

Still, it is the responsibility of those of us who understand the system to coax newcomers to  preserve it and use it efficiently.

Also Jim, If you like Aerosoft Lord Howe and ORBX, you should explore and apply the compatibility fix described at the FTX site and if you likeAero's Lord Howe you will probably also like Helgoland.
